article.description: — Jordan King's 34 points led Richmond past VMI 93-75 on Monday night in a season opener.
article.headline: King's 34 lead Richmond past VMI 93-75
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- — Jordan King's 34 points led Richmond past VMI 93-75 on Monday night in a season opener. King added five rebounds for the Spiders. Delonnie Hunt was 5-of-11 shooting, including 1 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 7 from the line to add 15 points. Jason Roche had nine points and shot 2 for 5 from beyond the arc and 3 of 4 from the free-throw line. The Keydets were led by Brennan Watkins, who recorded 24 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
